You will often see code like « somecmd ; if [[ $? = 0 ]] ; then ... ». Such code should be rewritten as « if somecmd ; then ... ». Likewise « somecmd ; if [[ $? != 0 ]] ; then ... » should be rewritten as « if ! somecmd ; then ... » (The special parameter ? (expanded by $?) holds the exit status of the last synchronous command, or (sometimes) 0 after an asynchronous command is started. It is an 8-bit integer (0-255) where 0 indicates
